        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51178",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=outeredge",
                        "name": "outeredge",
                        "displayName": "David Windell",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Error thrown is;\r\n\r\nlibrary\/Zend\/Mail\/Header\/GenericHeader.php:102 - Header name must start with a letter, and consist of only letters, numbers and dashes",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=outeredge",
                        "name": "outeredge",
                        "displayName": "David Windell",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-06-21T17:08:51.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-06-21T17:08:51.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51179",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=outeredge",
                        "name": "outeredge",
                        "displayName": "David Windell",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "After discussion on IRC with DASPRiD, suggestion was to have an option 'Ignore invalid headers'",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=outeredge",
                        "name": "outeredge",
                        "displayName": "David Windell",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-06-21T17:13:52.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-06-21T17:13:52.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51182",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=maks3w",
                        "name": "maks3w",
                        "displayName": "Maks 3w",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Invalid headers should throw an exception. Unknown headers should be implemented with GenericHeader\r\n\r\nFor me [from david@david.localdev.domain.com thu jun 21 16] it's not a From invalid header, its a header called \"from david@david.localdev.domain.com thu jun 21 16\"",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=maks3w",
                        "name": "maks3w",
                        "displayName": "Maks 3w",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-06-21T21:36:51.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-06-21T21:36:51.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51183",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=outeredge",
                        "name": "outeredge",
                        "displayName": "David Windell",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Our use case is a email being received from a pipe where custom headers such as the above may be inserted by the MTA. We don't want to have to pre-process the headers before calling addHeaders().\r\n\r\nHow do you propose this is implemented within GenericHeader, considering how the header \"[from david@david.localdev.domain.com thu jun 21 16]\" is so specific to the environment?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=outeredge",
                        "name": "outeredge",
                        "displayName": "David Windell",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-06-21T21:56:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-06-21T21:56:00.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51185",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=maks3w",
                        "name": "maks3w",
                        "displayName": "Maks 3w",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I checked the standard again and the first header can't be a valid field name because has spaces.\r\n\r\nI think that, in your case, ignore the first line from the input was enough.\r\n\r\nAnyway I opened this PR https:\/\/github.com\/zendframework\/zf2\/pull\/1549",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=maks3w",
                        "name": "maks3w",
                        "displayName": "Maks 3w",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-06-22T05:26:03.000+0000",
